title: Domestic passenger vehicle sales rise 11 pc in February: SIAM
description: In February, passenger vehicle wholesales in India increased by 11% year-on-year, with total dispatches reaching 3,70,786 units. Sports utility vehicles continued to drive demand, contributing to the highest-ever February sales for passenger vehicles. Two-wheeler sales rose 35% to 15,20,761 units, while three-wheeler dispatches increased to 54,584 units.
